9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 118, L.D. 185, “An Act to Expand
10 Opportunities to Invest Municipal Tax Increment Financing Revenues”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §5225, sub-§1, ¶C, as amended by PL 2023, c. 142, §§1 to
14 3, is further amended by amending subparagraph (9) to read:
15 (9) Costs related to the construction, renovation or operation of municipal or
16 plantation public safety facilities, including facilities used as emergency shelters,
17 the need for which is related to general economic development within the
18 municipality or plantation, not to exceed 15% 25% of the captured assessed value
19 of the development district;
20 Sec. 2. 30-A MRSA §5225, sub-§1, ¶C, as amended by PL 2023, c. 142, §§1 to
21 3, is further amended by amending subparagraph (12) to read:
22 (12) Up to 50% of the capital costs related to the construction or renovation of a
23 municipality's or plantation's central administrative office facilities owned by a
24 municipality or plantation and used to provide municipal or plantation services, the
25 need for which is related to general economic development within the municipality
26 or plantation, not to exceed 15% 25% of the captured assessed value of the
27 development district;'
28 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
29 number to read consecutively.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This amendment replaces the bill. It updates the limit of captured, assessed value of the
3322 development district that can be applied towards the construction, renovation and operation
3333 of public safety facilities, including facilities used as emergency shelters, in a municipality
3344 or plantation to 25%.
